{\listtext	\'95	}2 teaspoons superfine sugar\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 teaspoon fine sea salt\
{\listtext	\'95	}Juice of 1 lime\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 carrot, grated\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 seedless cucumber, peeled and thinly sliced\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 bunch scallion whites, finely chopped\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/4 cup fresh mint leaves\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 Fresno chile pepper, seeded and finely chopped\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural
\cf0 Whisk together the vinegar, sugar, sea salt and lime juice in a bowl until the sugar and salt have dissolved. Add the carrots, cucumbers and scallions, and toss to combine. Transfer the mixture to a plastic food storage container and refrigerate until ready to serve. Add the mint and chile pepper just before serving, and toss to combine.}